# Reality Check Step for Review Pipeline

## Goal
Add a new step that verifies blueprint data (specs, prices, legal info) against AI's knowledge **before** writing. Currently the pipeline trusts all data from the original script blindly.

## Proposed Changes

### Prompts
#### [NEW] [system_reality_check.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_reality_check.txt)
- AI receives the full blueprint JSON
- Cross-references every product's specs, pricing, and legal claims against its training knowledge
- Outputs structured JSON with:
  - `verified`: data that matches known facts
  - `suspicious`: data that may be outdated or incorrect (with AI's known value)
  - `outdated_pricing`: prices flagged as potentially outdated (with estimated current MSRP if known)
  - `discontinued`: products that may no longer be in production
  - `corrections`: suggested fixes with confidence level
- Special focus on **current pricing** (AI will flag if price seems old and suggest current MSRP)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> AI models don't have real-time internet access. This step leverages the model's training data (cutoff ~2024-2025). Prices newer than the training cutoff will be marked as "unable to verify" rather than flagged as wrong.

